,Recommended,464850,29396410,Posted: 21 January,all,GuyIncognito,"If you come into this game expecting cricket 2K17 or EA Sports Cricket then you will be disappointed, with more games than just this one.What I have found playing so far:Positives1. Batting is challenging and fun. It requires actual timing and skill.2. Bowler AI is much improved over DBC 14 and is constantly changing it up.3. My Career mode, player creation is much improved and offers greater depth.4. Visually better than DBC 14, yes the lighting is different but is more natural. (Grass blades people, grass!)5. Pitch variation: The pitches are much more dynamic this time around. Without saying much, you should pay attention to the pitch report as different bowler types will be more effective than others.6. Getting singles is much easier and more natural this time around, fielders are effective (most of the time - club cricketers are meant to be fairly average =) )7. Ball physics are much enhanced, although there are times where it bounces more than a tennis ball lol.8. Stadium creator is neat, could be a bit more robust but heu - Stadium creator!9. Customisation is quite remarkable from logos, teams, kits etc to setting up your grade league in my career (I reccomend creating a few rural type grounds for this part of the career as the defaults are proper stadiums. I don't recall my local team playing at the MCG lol.)Cons:1. Commentary is pretty bad, and by bad I mean horrendous. Fortunatly, if you mute it, the sound effects and ambience make for quite the relaxing time.2. A few visual bugs that I have encountered: namely, stuttered animations in fielding and replays. Not a biggie as I'm sure this will be fixed later.In Summary:If you like cricket and cricket likes you then DBC 17 is a fine game. Just for the love of god don't expect a 2K or EA game.Two thumbs up."
