76561198015006699,Not Recommended,464850,34531797,Posted: 27 August,all,cankercoot,"This game feels like a real step backwards from the previous DB title. It seems like the devs were more focused on delivering a game where you can alter every aspect of your career player's appearance or building your own cricket ground rather than an enjoyable cricket simulation. The difficulty has been ramped up for this iteration (no bad thing as cricket is a very hard game to master). This however has perhaps gone a little too far for back foot shots, as they seem near impossible to perfect. The AI for field settings is much better this time, it feels a bit more reactive and a bit more like the opposition have a 'plan' against you. However the AI for fielders is so bad; random slides, unnecessary throws to bowler's end, peculiar running around the ball, might be a simulation of club (or rather beer match!) cricket, but international fielders do not usually get up to such shenanigans. The commentary is truly awful. Lacklustre voice work that does nothing but sap your immersion in the game rather than bring added colour (if audio can do such a thing!?!) The wicketkeepers exhibit peculiar behaviour, flitting between being incompetant clowns to displaying superhuman athleticism (in one instance dismissing me by having me caught behind with a one handed catch in the position of a second slip, therefore diving fully across the guy at first slip!, to a spin bowler from a fierce back drive).If you want a fun cricket sim buy DB14, for all its flaws its still a superior game. If you want a frustrating and in the end unrewarding cricket sim then you've probably been on the staff for Big Ant and were part of the development team so therefore won't have to buy it. Otherwise don't buy this buggy mess of a game."
