76561198015082698,Recommended,464850,29454823,Posted: 23 January,all,AverageFreaq,"I absolutely love this game! I am not a regular reviewer of games despite gaming a lot and having a lot of games, so please stick with me if I ramble a bit.I finsihed with 994 hours of playtime on DB14 and I am sure I will clock even more playtime on this.I was really nervous buying this game with the mixed reviews that are on here but I decided to buy the game anyway as I remeber how good the dev team were at fixing issues on DB14 and my passion for cricket.  I needn't have been worried about anything.The batting brings a new challenge without changing too many of the things that made the last game so good.  I am still getting used to it but I get  a bit better with every innings, despite getting frustrated with myself for playing stupid shots (a lot like real life!)The bowling is a lot more rewarding than on DB14 where I felt sometimes it was too easy on the lower difficulties and was a bit of a boring slog on the harder difficulties, on this version I feel like I really get into the battle between batsmen and bowler. I read that the controls are a lot more difficult, but I have found them to be absolutely fine.The whole Career mode has had a revamp and it is fantastic, you earn SP points which you can use to level up certain batting/bowling/fielding attributes as you go along. You start off playing for a side local to the county you choose to play for and play in t20 matches for them until you are good enough to be selected for your county, you can also choose the batting and bowling difficulties independantly which is a fantastic idea.CONSI have only found two real negatives at the moment which are;1. The game randomly crashes when loading up a match (averaging once for every 10 hours of game time so far)2. The wording in the game, you can use shorter or longer pitch bowling. This annoys me everytime I see it, obviously longer is the opposite of shorter but in the context of cricket it should be shorter or fuller pitch bowling!PROS1. Graphics - smoother, better and easier for the PC to handle than DB142. Batting -  more challenging and rewarding, you get yourself out playing the wrong shots3. Bowling - more rewarding and more fun4. Career Mode - Everything about it, brilliant ideas, brilliantly executed by the devs5. James Taylor on commentary - nice touch and hasn't got too repeatetive on me yetAll in all I fully recommend this game for anyone. Cricket lovers, DB14 lovers and people new to cricket will all love this game and it is fully worth the pricetag.8/10 as it stands with the potential of being 10/10 and one of my favourite games of all time."
