76561198033186892,Recommended,464850,29708543,Posted: 4 February,all,barto_123,"If you like cricket, then you will love this game.To veterans coming from Don Bradman 14, the changes in this game will be immediately noticeable. The bowling feels so much more compelling than in the previous game, edges are satisfying to watch, and the AI batting is much improved. When batting, the increased range of strokes makes it so much more fluent to play, and more of the shots feel useable, unlike in the previous game.The graphics are a letdown, whilst jarring at first, with character models appearing somewhat more cartoony than the previous game, the improvements to the animations, environments and lighting engine overall give it a nicer and realistic feel, though somewhat lacking compared to other triple A sporting titles on the market.The improved career mode is a godsend, injecting so much more life to playing as your own pro, with the introduction of dynamic teams and club cricket. It feels satisfying to work your way up from the bottom to the top, and the difficulty adjustments you can make on the way allow you to tailor the game to your liking.Some bugs do persist though, with AI fields in first class games to reacting quick enough to your shot placement, allowing you to continually score into vacant gaps and not reacting and plugging them. It’s easily possible to score very quick runs with low skilled batsmen into these gaps. This was a bug in the previous game, so it’s frustrating to see it carry over to this game, three years on.Overall, it’s a great cricket experience. The best cricket game ever made, and well worth a look."
