,Not Recommended,464850,29647221,Posted: 2 February,all,champdood,"17 hours into this so far and am giving up until bug fixes come along. With a game like cricket, bowling to a strategy only to see your perfect LBW not called because according to the game it hit outside off stump (it didn't) is far more of a deal breaker than you'd think.Pros:The fielding isn't insane in this game. No fielders running at 200mph to take a catch compared to DB14Bowling is actually compelling and fun. You get mostly punished for crap bowling and rewarded for mixing it upVisualisations (reviews, batting movements) improvedGood overall game.Cons:Commentary is utterly attrocious. Very little variation and it's often flat out wrong.LBW ""hit outside off stump"" when it obviously did hit in the line. Plum LBWs regularly missed.Inconsistent gameplay. Last 4 games I edged a shot where I had perfect footwork, shot selection and timing. Basically the same shot 4 times over. Then I'll hit a shot with bad footwork and timing for 4.Fielders never throw to the end that makes logical sense (throw to the keeper unless there's a runout chance, they seem to do the opposite)Spinner fielding off their own bowling. Will stand there like a hapless idiot as the ball rolls past their feetLoad times are really bad for a simple game, especially career mode where you'll play a lot of games back to backRunning between wickets, don't put bat down until after reaching the end, hard to trigger second runs early on so you don't know what will happen. Kind of imaginary timing going on that's a game in itself.Recommend buying it in a few months.Additional thoughts: So a few weeks on, no bug patches and it becomes obvious that the bugs are pretty buried throughout the game. A lot of this makes no sense. So many bad LBW calls (even on review). The D/L method is broken in T20 matches. Batting turns into a frustrating mess when your batsman times it perfectly, with the perfect shot, only to get yet another edge. Some incredible graphic glitches - pitch was so bright I couldn't play at one point (looked like someone cranked the sun to about 3000%) mixed with some bizarre fielding (the tap back from the rope is great, that the player won't turn around and throw themselves is not so great). Some simple gameplay tweaks and adjustments would go a long way to make this game more enjoyable and less frustrating"
